impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/MorphismProperty/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty\">MorphismProperty</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A property of morphisms `P` is said to pre-ind-spread if `P`-morphisms out of filtered colimits\ndescend to a finite level. More precisely, let `Dᵢ` be a filtered family of objects.\nThen:\n\n- If `f : colim Dᵢ ⟶ T` satisfies `P`, there exists an index `j` and a pushout square\n  ```\n    Dⱼ ----f'---> T'\n    |             |\n    |             |\n    v             v\n  colim Dᵢ --f--> T\n  ```\n  such that `f'` satisfies `P`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/MorphismProperty/Ind.html#CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty.PreIndSpreads","kind":"class","line":159,"name":"CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty.PreIndSpreads","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/MorphismProperty/Ind.lean#L159-L179"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/MorphismProperty/Ind.html#CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty.ind_iff_exists\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">MorphismProperty</span>.<span class=\"name\">ind_iff_exists</span></a></span><span class=